## Custom Property Editors (CPE) for Experience Builder

When creating LWCs that expose `<property>` entries in `js-meta.xml`, evaluate whether a CPE would improve admin configuration. GA as of Spring '26.

### When to build a CPE

| Property pattern | CPE solution |
|---|---|
| String with fixed values (e.g. `cardType`) | Visual picker or button group |
| String for icon reference | Icon picker / browser |
| String for SF object/field API name | Schema-populated dropdown |
| Integer with min/max range | Slider with labels |
| Multiple related properties | Custom Property Type with tabs/accordions |
| Conditionally visible property | CPE with conditional rendering |

### Implementation

- Target `lightning__PropertyEditor` in `js-meta.xml`
- Public properties: `label`, `description`, `required`, `value`, `errors`, `schema`
- Dispatch `CustomEvent('valuechange', { detail: { value } })` on change
- For grouped panels: use `ExperiencePropertyTypeBundle` with `schema.json` + `design.json`

